KwaZulu-Natal police have re-arrested three of the five prisoners who escaped from the Margate police station. Police spokesperson Lieutenant-Colonel Thulani Zwane said the five awaiting-trial prisoners escaped from the cells on Sunday. Zwane said they had been arrested for serious crimes such as murder and a string of robberies. One man was re-arrested at Nyandezulu location in the Paddock area and two others handed themselves in at Gamalakhe police station. Two other men are still on the run.